WEBVTT

00:00.384 --> 00:02.418
<i>Previously on "Heartland":</i>

00:04.554 --> 00:06.022
<i>Phoenix!</i>

00:06.991 --> 00:09.001
Lisa! Oh my gosh!

00:11.595 --> 00:13.395
I thought I was picking you up
at the airport.

00:13.462 --> 00:14.562
Yeah, I caught an earlier flight

00:14.630 --> 00:16.331
because I couldn't wait to see you.

00:16.399 --> 00:19.367
When I first showed up here
with Shane, last year,

00:19.435 --> 00:21.770
you made it perfectly clear
that any relationship

00:21.838 --> 00:23.005
<i>wasn't gonna happen.</i>

00:23.072 --> 00:24.506
Well, I don't...

00:24.573 --> 00:25.607
Who are you?

00:25.675 --> 00:27.309
Cassandra Fay.

00:27.376 --> 00:28.810
<i>I'm Scott's new vet assistant.</i>

00:32.080 --> 00:33.314
Who are you?

00:33.381 --> 00:35.283
And what are you doing on my horse?

00:41.090 --> 00:43.124
<i>Come on, Spartan.</i>

00:43.192 --> 00:44.459
Ugh! That kid!

00:46.528 --> 00:48.596
Hey! Georgie!

00:48.664 --> 00:49.930
Do you have a death wish or something?

00:49.998 --> 00:52.299
Amy doesn't let anyone
ride Spartan -

00:52.368 --> 00:54.134
no one, not even me.

00:54.202 --> 00:56.804
Maybe. But she let me.

00:56.872 --> 00:58.339
Or maybe, you're delusional.

00:58.407 --> 00:59.841
Do yourself a favour

00:59.908 --> 01:01.475
and get off that horse
before Amy catches you.

01:01.542 --> 01:03.309
No way.
It was her idea,

01:03.378 --> 01:04.911
and she said if I get really good

01:04.979 --> 01:06.380
she'll give me jumping lessons.

01:06.447 --> 01:08.114
Yeah, right.

01:08.182 --> 01:09.983
You don't believe me, ask her.

01:10.050 --> 01:13.019
Did you say she
could ride Spartan?

01:13.087 --> 01:15.822
She won't believe me
that you let me ride your horse.

01:15.890 --> 01:18.624
Well, why don't you get
riding him then, hmm?

01:20.927 --> 01:22.995
You're giving
her jumping lessons,

01:23.062 --> 01:24.697
but not me?

01:24.765 --> 01:26.298
<i>Since when do you
want jumping lessons?</i>

01:26.366 --> 01:27.466
You don't remember?

01:27.534 --> 01:29.668
I used to beg you to teach me to jump.

01:29.736 --> 01:30.770
Well, yeah, I remember,

01:30.837 --> 01:32.504
but that was ages ago.

01:32.571 --> 01:33.705
And besides, I thought
that had something to do

01:33.773 --> 01:35.973
with Jake and some girl.

01:36.041 --> 01:37.675
Way to dredge up the past.

01:37.743 --> 01:40.244
Well, I just didn't feel like
you were very committed.

01:40.312 --> 01:41.513
Maybe then.

01:41.580 --> 01:42.947
But now, I have gone
from commitment-phobe

01:43.015 --> 01:44.783
to commitment freak.

01:44.850 --> 01:46.618
Really.
You jumping.

01:47.620 --> 01:49.420
When do we start?

01:52.256 --> 01:54.124
Well, good morning.

01:54.191 --> 01:56.627
Hi. I should've called, sorry.

01:56.694 --> 01:58.328
No. I'm happy to see you.

01:58.396 --> 01:59.696
Here, let me get you a coffee.

01:59.764 --> 02:01.732
No. I've had plenty, thanks.

02:01.800 --> 02:03.600
I know, it's not the good stuff

02:03.668 --> 02:05.568
we used to drink in France.

02:05.636 --> 02:08.002
Speaking of France...

02:08.071 --> 02:10.072
Oh! That's a...
some kind of TV.

02:10.139 --> 02:12.875
No. It's a digital
picture frame.

02:12.943 --> 02:15.778
I downloaded all our pictures
from France.

02:15.846 --> 02:17.012
It has...

02:17.080 --> 02:19.114
Music.

02:20.850 --> 02:22.216
Isn't that great?

02:22.284 --> 02:23.217
Isn't that better than pictures
in an album?

02:23.285 --> 02:24.352
Jack!

02:24.420 --> 02:26.254
You busy?
Oh! Hi, Lisa.

02:26.322 --> 02:27.956
Hi.

02:28.023 --> 02:29.624
What do we have here?

02:29.692 --> 02:32.994
<i>Is this a music video</i>
<i>of your trip to France,</i>

02:33.062 --> 02:34.429
starring - ahh! - You!

02:36.365 --> 02:38.198
What do you want?

02:38.266 --> 02:41.234
Oh, Miranda and Shane
are coming by today.

02:41.302 --> 02:42.570
Oh, congratulations!

02:42.637 --> 02:44.204
I heard that Shane got into
an exclusive school.

02:44.272 --> 02:46.006
Exclusive and expensive.

02:46.942 --> 02:51.244
<i>You know, which is why I need</i>
<i>to talk to old Jacques here.</i>

02:51.312 --> 02:52.645
Right now?

02:52.713 --> 02:53.980
Well... uh...

02:55.483 --> 02:56.983
Yeah... r-right now.

02:57.651 --> 02:59.719
In fact, really right away

02:59.787 --> 03:01.521
'cause I'm busy later.

03:01.589 --> 03:02.822
Oh, all right.

03:05.392 --> 03:06.359
We won't be too long.

03:06.426 --> 03:08.494
Oh, of course not.

03:10.797 --> 03:12.998
<i>So how long does
that thing run anyway?</i>

03:13.065 --> 03:15.934
Plugged in,
it'll run on a loop forever.

03:16.002 --> 03:18.169
Whoa!
Is that right?

03:19.138 --> 03:21.540
What side is the right ventricle on?

03:21.608 --> 03:23.509
It's on the right side.

03:23.576 --> 03:25.309
Correct!

03:25.377 --> 03:27.344
Caleb, you gotta ask me a
real question, man. Come on.

03:27.412 --> 03:29.680
Explain to me the flow of blood
through the heart.

03:29.748 --> 03:31.415
Okay, um...

03:32.350 --> 03:34.585
Deoxigenated blood from the body

03:34.653 --> 03:37.154
enters the right atrium
through the superior

03:37.222 --> 03:38.122
and inferior vena cava-

03:39.658 --> 03:42.592
Like anybody actually knows
how the damn thing works.

03:42.660 --> 03:43.927
What're you talking about?

03:43.995 --> 03:45.962
The same thing you are, my friend.

03:46.030 --> 03:49.599
The heart - the mysteries
of the human heart.

03:49.667 --> 03:51.167
Caleb, this isn't a joke, man.

03:51.235 --> 03:52.936
I gotta learn this stuff,
okay? Come on.

03:53.004 --> 03:54.838
Oh? Well, try being a bull rider
on the circuit.

03:54.906 --> 03:56.172
You know, the average age
is twenty-one.

03:56.240 --> 03:58.040
That puts me four years past my prime,

03:58.107 --> 04:00.175
and that is not an easy thing
for any man to comprehend.

04:00.243 --> 04:01.476
Okay, um...

04:01.545 --> 04:02.778
I'd love to have
this conversation with you

04:02.846 --> 04:04.146
right now...

04:04.213 --> 04:05.614
I need to shine.
I've gotta peak this year.

04:05.682 --> 04:07.215
And I will have this conversation

04:07.283 --> 04:09.018
after my exam.

04:10.887 --> 04:13.555
It's not just the tuition, Jack.

04:13.622 --> 04:15.657
It's the uniform
and the class trips-

04:15.724 --> 04:17.458
So what, you brought me
all the way out here

04:17.526 --> 04:19.260
just to tell me you're broke?

04:19.327 --> 04:20.928
You want me to take you
back to the Maison?

04:20.995 --> 04:22.463
You can look at a few more
pictures of France with Lisa.

04:22.531 --> 04:23.731
Fine! Fine.

04:24.833 --> 04:26.100
Just let's get this over with.

04:26.168 --> 04:27.735
Okay, don't look.

04:28.670 --> 04:31.038
What if I told you that
there was a healthy red meat

04:31.105 --> 04:33.006
with all the flavour of beef,

04:33.074 --> 04:35.709
raised locally, sold locally,

04:35.777 --> 04:37.010
one hundred percent organic.

04:37.078 --> 04:38.411
It's where the smart money is,

04:38.479 --> 04:40.413
and it's a sure thing.

04:40.481 --> 04:42.282
You own race horses, Tim,

04:42.349 --> 04:44.051
you oughta know there's
no such thing as a sure thing.

04:44.118 --> 04:46.318
But if there was?

04:49.656 --> 04:50.723
You're looking at it.

04:54.061 --> 04:55.494
Buffalo.

04:55.562 --> 04:57.162
Some call it buffalo,
some call it bison.

04:57.230 --> 04:58.564
You can call it whatever you want,

04:58.632 --> 05:01.132
but I am gonna call
that big fella our future.

05:01.200 --> 05:03.635
And that is your retirement in France.

05:03.703 --> 05:05.737
Who said anything about retirement?

05:05.805 --> 05:09.774
Oh yeah, I wanna work
till the day we drop too.

05:09.842 --> 05:10.976
Get serious.

05:11.043 --> 05:13.111
We buy this bull and a couple of cows,

05:13.178 --> 05:16.147
we are in the organic
bison meat business,

05:16.215 --> 05:18.882
<i>and we are printing money.</i>

05:19.851 --> 05:22.086
Come on, what do you say?

05:22.153 --> 05:26.724
Well, there's no doubt
that is one fine looking animal.

05:28.727 --> 05:32.362
But I've been burned by you
in the past.

05:32.430 --> 05:34.330
Okay. But...

05:36.834 --> 05:39.936
Can't we be bullish about the future?

